<$fill $name="body">

!! Schema model

|!Schema element |!Discovery filter |!Key fields |
|Type |`[rrt.type[type]]` |key, icon, parent, upref, `rrt.fields:0()` |
|Field |`[rrt.type[field]]` |key, typed, constraints, validity |
|Enum |`[rrt.type[enum]]` |key, parent, `rrt.options:0()` |

!! Inheritance

Single parent via `parent` field. Base type `_node` defines common fields + aggregator `rrt.fields()`. Subtypes add `rrt.fields:1()` and optionally `:2`, and may also override `rrt.fields:0()` to drop inherited base fields. Same pattern for enums (`rrt.options:0`/`:1`/`:2`).

Parent type variables are imported before the subtype's, so subtype slot definitions take precedence over the parent's — this is what enables the `:0` override.

!! Field bar

The field bar (both `viewtemplate-fields` and `field-bar-inline`) starts with the type icon, which acts as an identifier/hover for the entity. Hovering shows `type-key: caption` (falls back to tiddler title if no caption).

!! Object-reference editor modes

Object-ref fields (typed as entity type keys) support two editor modes, configurable via `$:/config/rimir/typed/ref-editor`:

* ''Typeahead'' (default) — search input with filtered dropdown. Better for large option sets. Selected values shown as compact tags below the input. Searches across title, caption, subtitle, and abbrev simultaneously.
* ''Pills'' — all options rendered as clickable pill buttons with optional inline filter. Better for small option sets (also used for enum fields regardless of config).

The display field for both modes is controlled by `$:/config/rimir/typed/pill-display` (title, caption, subtitle, or abbrev).

!! Field resolution

* Multiple field tiddlers can share the same `key`
* `validity` field restricts a definition to specific types (most-specific wins)
* `typed` controls the editor: `text`, `date`, `enum:<key>`, type keys (object refs), `$title`, `$calculated`

!! Constraints

|!Constraint |!Meaning |
|`n:1` |Single select |
|`!N+` |Min N required (blocking) |
|`N+` |Min N required (warning) |
|`!u` |Unique wiki-wide (blocking) |
|`u` |Unique wiki-wide (warning) |
|`filter` |Title computation formula |

!! Shared infrastructure

* ''functions.tid'' — all shared functions: field lookup (`_locate_rrt`), validation, helpers
* ''field-editor.tid'' — reusable per-field editor template (handles enum/text/date/object + validation)

!! UI components

* ''Spawner flow'': select type → `$importvariables` pulls functions + type + parent → `rrt.fields()` merges all levels → per field: locate definition, render editor (or `$title`/`$calculated` special handling)
* ''Validator flow'': per non-abstract type → per instance: check min/unique/title/calculated constraints → red (blocking) or orange (warning)
* ''Field Bar flow'': only for tiddlers with `rrt.type` field → per field: compact cell (icon + truncated value), click opens popup with `field-editor`

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">Uniqueness constraints (`!u`/`u`) are wiki-wide — they check all tiddlers, not just same-type instances.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
